1
00:00:00,075 --> 00:00:09,775
Docker is a popular platform as a service  PaaS  product that utilizes OS-level virtualization to deliver software in packages called containers

2
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:11,600
Containers are isolated

3
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:13,125
with their own software

4
00:00:13,412 --> 00:00:14,238
libraries

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,325
and configuration files

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:20,200
but they can communicate with each other through well-defined channels

7
00:00:20,613 --> 00:00:21,600
By using Docker

8
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:26,087
developers can automate the deployment of applications inside lightweight

9
00:00:26,337 --> 00:00:30,425
portable containers that can run consistently on various environments

